ordered-list.list-item:
Edit the configuration file for the nginx reverse proxy, which is located in the directory /etc/nginx/conf.d. Redirect traffic away from the Sync Gateway node that you will upgrade, distributing the traffic over the remaining nodes. Following are before and after examples of the upstream directive in the nginx configuration file. In this example, we upgrade node 41 first.
Before:

upstream sync_gateway {
server 172.20.30.41:4984;
server 172.20.30.42:4984;
server 172.20.30.43:4984;
}

After:

upstream sync_gateway {
server 172.20.30.41:4984 down;
server 172.20.30.42:4984;
server 172.20.30.43:4984;
}

Note that the distribution of traffic will change from one-third of the traffic on each of three nodes (41, 42, and 43) to one-half of the traffic on each of two nodes (42 and 43).

Edit the configuration file for the nginx reverse proxy, which is located in the directory /etc/nginx/conf.d. Redirect traffic to all Sync Gateway nodes except the one that you plan to upgrade next. Following are before and after examples of the upstream directive in the nginx configuration file. In this case, we plan to upgrade node 42 next.
Before:

upstream sync_gateway {
    server 172.20.30.41:4984;
    server 172.20.30.42:4984;
    server 172.20.30.43:4984 down;
}

After:

upstream sync_gateway {
    server 172.20.30.41:4984;
    server 172.20.30.42:4984;
    server 172.20.30.43:4984;
}
